  <element>
    <id>UMLNote</id>
    <coordinates>
      <x>20</x>
      <y>20</y>
      <w>2860</w>
      <h>140</h>
    </coordinates>
    <panel_attributes>Domain model (group) - Level B (built on Level C)
--
Goal: keep Level C changes minimal; add Level B entities/relations on top.
Pattern in Level C components:
- 1 Role -&gt; * Main Entity
- 1 Main Entity -&gt; * Child Entity (composition)
- Main Entity cannot be published without &gt;= 1 Child Entity
- startMoment/endMoment define a valid interval; when publishing, the interval must be in the future
- /monthsActive is derived
- Main Entity has a derived aggregate (cost/effort/expectedPercentage/totalMoney/hours)

Mapping (Level C):
- C01: Inventor -&gt; Invention -&gt; Part
- C02: Spokesperson -&gt; Campaign -&gt; Milestone
- C03: Fundraiser -&gt; Strategy -&gt; Tactic
- C04: Sponsor -&gt; Sponsorship -&gt; Donation
- C05: Auditor -&gt; AuditReport -&gt; AuditSection

bg=#f3fdff</panel_attributes>
    <additional_attributes/>
  </element>

  <element>
    <id>UMLNote</id>
